message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for question answering tasks, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks and fine-tuning of pre-trained models also suggests potential relevance to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of contextualized embeddings and attention mechanisms for language modeling may also relate to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
